      "rag_context": "[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"{\\\"pageContent\\\":\\\"Pipeline velocity benchmarks for technical hiring. Industry average time-to-hire by role: Software Engineer 35-45 days, Senior Engineer 42-52 days, Staff/Principal 55-70 days, Data Scientist 40-55 days. Interview-to-offer conversion benchmark: 35-45% (current dataset: 28.5% — below benchmark). Offer-to-acceptance conversion benchmark: 72-78% (current: 59.6% — below benchmark). Sourcing-to-screen conversion: typically 20-30% of applicants reach phone screen. Pipeline health score formula: (Offer rate × Acceptance rate) / SLA compliance × 100.\\\",\\\"metadata\\\":{\\\"agent\\\":\\\"pipeline_health\\\",\\\"category\\\":\\\"velocity_metrics\\\"},\\\"id\\\":\\\"pipe-004\\\"}\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"{\\\"pageContent\\\":\\\"Time-to-hire SLA benchmarks by position level. Mid-level roles: SLA target 21-28 days from application to offer. Senior roles: SLA target 28-35 days. Lead roles: SLA target 35-42 days. Staff roles: SLA target 35-45 days. Principal roles: SLA target 42-55 days. Average rounds by level in this dataset: Lead 3.32, Senior 3.01, Mid 2.84, Principal 2.54, Staff 2.39. Staff has fewer rounds but longer calendar time due to scheduling complexity. Every reschedule adds 3-5 days; 50% of candidates had 2+ reschedules — expect pipeline to run long.\\\",\\\"metadata\\\":{\\\"agent\\\":\\\"pipeline_health\\\",\\\"category\\\":\\\"sla_benchmarks_by_level\\\"},\\\"id\\\":\\\"pipe-002\\\"}\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"{\\\"pageContent\\\":\\\"SLA breach indicators and escalation thresholds. Amber alert: role open for 80% of SLA with no offer stage reached. Red alert: role breaches SLA with no accepted offer. Common SLA breach causes: interviewer unavailability (reschedules), delayed debrief meetings, slow hiring manager response on offer approval. Roles with 3+ reschedules are 2.4x more likely to breach SLA. Benchmark: SLA breach rate should be under 15% of open roles. Recommended action: weekly pipeline review for all roles past 60% of SLA target. Automated nudges to hiring managers at 70% and 85% of SLA window.\\\",\\\"metadata\\\":{\\\"agent\\\":\\\"pipeline_health\\\",\\\"category\\\":\\\"sla_breach_indicators\\\"},\\\"id\\\":\\\"pipe-005\\\"}\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"{\\\"pageContent\\\":\\\"Pipeline bottleneck analysis. Round 2 has highest rejection rate (31 rejections, 27.2%) — technical screen is primary filter. If Round 2 is async/take-home: high dropout may indicate poor candidate experience, not skill gap. Rescheduling is a significant bottleneck: 51% of candidates had 2-3 reschedules, adding 6-15 days to average time-to-hire. Role cancellations (15) mid-pipeline waste 15+ candidate-slots and damage employer brand. Recommendation: freeze headcount approval must precede JD posting, not follow it.\\\",\\\"metadata\\\":{\\\"agent\\\":\\\"pipeline_health\\\",\\\"category\\\":\\\"bottleneck_identification\\\"},\\\"id\\\":\\\"pipe-003\\\"}\"}]",
